# Task Management (taskmd)

This platform repo is the **single source of truth** for all task management across all apps (card, stocks, platform). Tasks live in `tasks/` as individual markdown files with YAML frontmatter. Managed via [taskmd](https://github.com/driangle/taskmd).

## Reading tasks for context

When looking for work or understanding project priorities, only read tasks where `status` is `pending` or `in-progress`. Ignore `completed`, `cancelled`, and `blocked` tasks unless specifically asked about them.

## Task file format

Each task is a standalone `.md` file with YAML frontmatter:

```yaml
---
id: "001"
title: "Short descriptive title"
status: pending          # pending | in-progress | in-review | completed | blocked | cancelled
group: card              # card | stocks | platform  (REQUIRED — which app this task belongs to)
phase: card              # must match group — shows in the PHASE column of the list view
priority: medium         # low | medium | high | critical
type: feature            # feature | bug | improvement | chore | docs
tags: [relevant, tags]
dependencies: ["003"]    # optional: IDs of tasks that must complete first
effort: medium           # optional: small | medium | large
created: YYYY-MM-DD
---
```

The `group` and `phase` fields are required on every task and must have the same value. Valid values: `card`, `stocks`, `platform`. `group` enables "Group by: Group" in the Board view. `phase` shows the app in the PHASE column of the list view and enables the Phases view for per-app progress tracking.

The markdown body should include Purpose/Objective and Approach/Acceptance Criteria sections.

## Creating a task

Use descriptive filenames: `ID-short-slug.md` (e.g., `007-add-caching-layer.md`). Use sequential IDs zero-padded to 3 digits. Always set both the `group` and `phase` fields to the same app value. If the app association is ambiguous (e.g., cross-cutting work), prompt the user to specify.

## Completing a task

Set `status: completed` in the frontmatter. Do not delete the file.

## Spinning up the task dashboard

To start the taskmd web dashboard:

```sh
taskmd web start --dir tasks/ --open --port 4173
```

Run this from the platform repo root (`haderach-platform/`). The binary is installed at `~/bin/taskmd`. The dashboard opens at `http://localhost:4173`.

## Cross-repo task creation

When working in an app repo (card, stocks) and a task needs to be created, write the task file to the platform repo at `../haderach-platform/tasks/`. Set the `group` field to match the app being worked on. The sibling layout under `haderach_site/` is relied upon: `haderach_site/{card,stocks,haderach-platform}`.
